    <h2 id="why-sugar-free">Why Sugar-Free Creatine Gummies Matter for Performance Athletes</h2>

    <p>Creatine monohydrate is the single most studied and validated sports supplement in history, with over 500 peer-reviewed studies confirming its ability to increase phosphocreatine stores, enhance ATP regeneration during high-intensity exercise, and support lean muscle mass gains. The scientific consensus is overwhelming: 3-5g of creatine daily improves strength, power output, and lean mass. But the gummy delivery format introduces a problem — binding creatine into gummy form typically requires sugar (sucrose, glucose syrup) to create the texture and stability consumers expect. Standard creatine gummies contain 4-8g of sugar per daily dose (equivalent to 1-2 teaspoons), which adds 16-32 unnecessary calories and can disrupt ketosis for low-carb athletes.</p>

    <div class="key-stat">
