      <div class="warn-box-ico"><Icon name="warning" size={18} /></div>
      <p><strong>Sugar alcohols (erythritol, maltitol, sorbitol) can cause digestive discomfort.</strong> While most sugar-free creatine gummies are well-tolerated, products using erythritol or other sugar alcohols may cause bloating, gas, or loose stools in sensitive individuals — especially at higher doses needed for full 5g creatine intake. If you experience digestive issues, switch to formulations using allulose or monk fruit, which do not cause gastrointestinal side effects.</p>
    </div>

